<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Breadfruit Legacy</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

  <style>
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      color: #f1f5f9;

      /* 🌿 Background image */
      background-image: url('breadfruit.jpg');
      background-size: cover;
      background-position: center;
      background-attachment: fixed;
    }

    /* Dark overlay so text is readable */
    .overlay {
      background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
      min-height: 100vh;
      padding: 20px;
    }

    header {
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 28px;
      font-weight: bold;
      padding: 20px;
      color: #22c55e;
    }

    section {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: auto;
    }

    .scene {
      background: rgba(30, 41, 59, 0.8);
      padding: 15px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      border-radius: 10px;
    }

    .label {
      color: #22c55e;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    footer {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 20px;
      font-size: 14px;
      opacity: 0.8;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>

<div class="overlay">

<header>
  Breadfruit Legacy 🌿
</header>

<section>

  <div class="scene">
    <p class="label">Opening:</p>
    <p>The breadfruit tree stands tall in the Caribbean sun...</p>
  </div>

  <div class="scene">
    <p class="label">Meaning:</p>
    <p>A symbol of food, culture, and survival across generations.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="scene">
    <p class="label">Nutrition:</p>
    <p>Rich in fiber, carbs, and potassium.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="scene">
    <p class="label">Closing:</p>
    <p>More than a tree — it is a legacy.</p>
  </div>

</section>

<footer>
  © Breadfruit Legacy Project
</footer>

</div>

</body>
</html>
